{{italic title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox film |name=''Poétique du cerveau'' |film name=''Poetics of the Brain'' |image=Poétique du cerveau poster.jpg |caption=DVD cover art |director=[[Nurith Aviv]] |writer=Nurith Aviv |producer={{Flat list|*Serge Lalou *Farid Rezkallah *Itai Tamir}} |editing={{Flat list|*Amir Borenstein *Laure Saint-Marc}} |narrator=Nurith Aviv |starring={{Flat list|*Prof. Dr. François Ansermet *Nurith Aviv *Prof. Dr. {{ill|Laurent Cohen|fr}} *Prof. Dr. [[Yadin Dudai]] *Prof. Dr. [[Vittorio Gallese]] *Dr. Sharon Andrea Peperkamp *Prof. Dr. Noam Sobel}} |music={{ill|Werner Hasler|de}} |cinematography={{Flat list|*Nurith Aviv *Sophie Cadet *Itai Marom}} |studio={{Flat list|*24 Images Production *Angoa-[[Association of International Collective Management of Audiovisual Works]] *[[Arte]] *{{ill|Les Films d’ici|fr|Les Films d'ici}} *[[KTO (TV channel)|KTO]] *Laïla Films *[[Ministry of Culture and Sport (Israel)|Ministry of Culture and Sport]]’s Israel Film Council *[[National Center of Cinematography and the moving image|National Center of Cinematography and the Moving Image]] *{{ill|Procirep|fr}} *{{ill|Conseil régional des Pays de la Loire|ca|Consell Regional del País del Loira|fr}} *Scam – Brouillon d’un rêve *Yahel Leon Recanati Foundation *{{ill|Yehoshua Rabinovich Foundation for the Arts, Tel Aviv|he|קרן יהושע רבינוביץ לאמנויות תל אביב}} *[[ZDF]]}} |distributor=Margo Cinéma |released={{Film date|df=y|2015|12|02|{{ill|Les 3 Luxembourg|fr}}}} |runtime=66 minutes |country={{Flat list|*France *Germany *Israel}} |language={{Flat list|*French *Hebrew *Italian}}}} '''''Poétique du cerveau''''' (English: ''Poetics of the Brain'') is a 66-minute 2015 French-German-Israeli French-, Hebrew-, and Italian-language independent underground experimental documentary art film directed by Nurith Aviv.
==Synopsis== Childhood photos from Nurith Aviv’s family album evoke memories and reflections which lead her to encounters with researches in neuroscience. The film, released on DVD by Epicentre Films,<ref>{{cite AV media|url=http://www.epicentrefilms.com/dvd-Poetique-du-cerveau-Nurith|people=Aviv, Nurith|title=Poétique du cerveau|location=Paris|publisher=Epicentre Films|language=French|accessdate=26 April 2018|format=DVD|oclc=949902028|date=26 April 2016|trans-title=Poetics of the Brain}}</ref> weaves associative links between Aviv’s personal biographical stories and interviews she conducts with neuroscientists about their work. These scientists, including Prof. Dr. Laurent Cohen, Prof. Dr. Yadin Dudai, and Prof. Dr. Vittorio Gallese, discuss topics partly related to Aviv’s previous films: memory, bilingualism, reading, mirror-neurons, smell, and traces of experience.
==Reception== The film, which includes music by Werner Hasler and was financed ''inter alia'' by Les Films d’ici, Angoa-Association of International Collective Management of Audiovisual Works, KTO, Conseil régional des Pays de la Loire, ZDF, Arte, National Center of Cinematography and the Moving Image, Procirep, Ministry of Culture and Sport’s Israel Film Council, and Yehoshua Rabinovich Foundation for the Arts, Tel Aviv, was screened at Les 3 Luxembourg in 2015 and 2016, at [[Centre Georges Pompidou]] in 2015, and at [[Docaviv|DocAviv]], [[Tel Aviv Cinematheque]], Arte, and {{ill| Cinema South International Film Festival|he|פסטיבל קולנוע דרום}} in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bar-On|first=Yaakov|date=19 December 2016|script-title=he:נשארת בתמונה|trans-title=She Stays in the Picture|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/MAARIV_2016.pdf|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''[[The Jerusalem Post]]''|pages=10–11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Esterkin|first=Jonathan|script-title=he:שפת המוח|trans-title=Language of the Brain|date=15 May 2016|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/maariv1505.jpg|language=Hebrew|work=Maariv|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''The Jerusalem Post''}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hupertz|first=Dr. Heike|script-title=Haben wir uns darüber schon mal Gedanken gemacht?|trans-title=Have We Ever Given It Some Thought?|date=13 June 2016|url=https://www.faz.net/dokumentarfilm-poetik-des-gehirns-bei-arte-14283050|language=German|work=[[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]]|location=Frankfurt am Main|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung Gesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Haverkamp|first=Susanne|script-title=Arte-Doku zeigt Neues aus der Gehirnforschung|trans-title=Arte Documentary Presents News Regarding Neuroscience|date=13 June 2016|url=https://www.noz.de/deutschland-welt/medien/artikel/727540/arte-doku-zeigt-neues-aus-der-gehirnforschung|language=German|work=[[Neue Osnabrücker Zeitung]]|location=Osnabrück|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Neue Osnabrücker Zeitung Gesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung und Compagnie Kommanditgesellschaft}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Riepe|first=Manfred|script-title=Ein filmisches Gedicht|trans-title=A Cinematic Poem|date=24 June 2016|url=https://www.medienkorrespondenz.de/fernsehen/artikel/nurith-aviv-poetik-desnbspgehirns-arte|language=German|work={{ill|Medienkorrespondenz|de}}|location=Bonn|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Dreipunktdrei Mediengesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|script-title=''Poetik des Gehirns''|trans-title=''Poetics of the Brain''|url=https://www.filmdienst.de/film/details/548135/poetik-des-gehirns|language=German|work={{ill|Filmdienst|de}}|location=Bonn|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=Dreipunktdrei Mediengesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Brant|first=Zohar|script-title=he:על '''פואטיקה של המוח'''|trans-title=Of ''Poetics of the Brain''|url=http://sff.sapir.ac.il/2016/csf.sapir.ac.il/indexe031.html|date=5–9 June 2016|language=Hebrew|location=Sderot|access-date=26 April 2018|publisher=[[Sapir Academic College]], School of Audio and Visual Arts}}</ref>
