{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Leo III by Rafael.jpg | title=The Oath of Leo III (detail) | image_size=175px | artist=Workshop of [[Raphael]] | year=1516–1517 | type=[[Fresco]] | dimensions={{convert|770|cm|in|abbr=on}} wide | city=[[Vatican City]] | museum=[[Apostolic Palace]] }}
'''''The Oath of Leo III''''' is a [[painting]] by the workshop of the [[Italy|Italian]] [[renaissance]] artist [[Raphael]]. The painting was part of Raphael's commission to decorate the rooms that are now known as the ''[[Raphael Rooms|Stanze di Raffaello]]'', in the [[Apostolic Palace]] in the [[Vatican City|Vatican]]. It is located in the room that was named after ''[[The Fire in the Borgo]]'', the ''Stanza dell'incendio del Borgo''. In the [[fresco]], [[Pope Leo III]] is seen during the trial on December 23 [[AD]] 800 during which he was brought face to face with the nephews of his predecessor [[Pope Hadrian I]], who had accused him of misconduct. The assembled bishops declared that they could not judge the pope, after which Leo took an oath of purgation of his own free will.<ref>[http://mv.vatican.va/3_EN/pages/x_Schede/SDRs/SDRs_04_02_029.html] vatican.va]</ref> ==References== {{reflist}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Oath Of Leo Iii}} [[Category:Raphael rooms]] [[Category:1517 paintings]] [[Category:Books in art]]
